    <text type="correspondence">
        <body>
            <div1>
                <pb facs="ccda.corr000216.001.jpg"/>
                
                <fw type="letterhead" place="top-left" hand="#h01">CHAS. W. CHESNUTT<lb/> Helen C. Moore</fw>
                <fw type="letterhead" place="top" hand="#h01">CHESNUTT &#38; MOORE<lb/> SHORTHAND REPORTERS<lb/> 1106 WILLIAMSON BUILDING<lb/> CLEVELAND</fw>
                
               
                <dateline><date when="1917-01-03"><add hand="#h02">March 27, 1923.</add></date></dateline>

                <opener>
                    
                <address>
                    <addrLine>The Editor of The Journal of Negro History,<note type="editorial" resp="#slg" n="2" target="#jnh"/></addrLine>
                    <addrLine>1538 Ninth Street</addrLine>
                    <addrLine>Washington, D. C.</addrLine>
                </address>
                    
                <salute>Dear Sir:
                </salute>
                    
            </opener>
                
                <p hand="#h02"><hi rend="underline">Attention Mr. S. W. Rutherford, Sec'y-Treas.<note type="editorial" resp="#slg" n="1" target="swr"/></hi></p>
                <p hand="#h02">I have your letter of February 26th, calling attention to the fact that your records show that my subscription expired with the 1922 number, and enclosing bill for $4.00 covering subscription from January, 1922, to January, 1924.</p>
                <p hand="#h02">My reference to my own records I find that on January 9, 1922, I sent you a check for $2.00 for subscription to the Journal one year in advance, and in return received your receipt dated January 10, 1922, reading as follows: "Received of Mr. Charles W. Chesnutt, $2.00 for renewal of subscription."  This would seem to indicate that your record in this respect is not correct, and that I owe you only $2.00, subscription for 1923 in advance, for which I enclose a check.  The Journal is serving a very useful prupose and I am very glad to get it, and read it with interest</p>
                
            <closer>
                <salute>Sincerely yours,</salute>
                <signed hand="#h03">Chas. W. Chesnutt.</signed>
            </closer>
                <note type="authorial" hand="#h02">CWC/FL</note>
            </div1>
            
        </body>
        
