                <affiliation>The Journal of Negro History</affiliation>
                <note>Samuel Wilson Rutherford was the Secretary-Treasurer of the Association for the Study of African American Life, which published the Journal of Negro History.  He was also a close friend of editor Woodson. Rutherford’s duties for the journal included managing subscription fees and accounts. With his experience and notoriety as a banker in Washington D.C., he was well known as a man of business (“Samuel Wilson Rutherford." The Journal of Negro History 37, no. 2 (1952): 216-17. JSTOR, http://www.jstor.org/stable/2715353).</note>
            </person>
